title.narrative: By 2022, the country will have the capacity to reduce under-recording of births in under-fives, supporting the nationwide implementation of the initiative for timely registration in hospitals.

description.narrative: The system strengthening, cross-sectoral work and political commitment increased the timely birth registration rate. As a result of the joint commitment promoted by UNICEF between the Presidency of the Republic, Central Electoral Board, Ministry of Health and National Health Service to implement the CRC recommendations for birth registration and SDG 16.9, the timely birth registration rate doubled from 41% in 2012 to 83%, in 2019 in prioritized hospitals. It means that 60,071 children have a better chance of thriving in life. Nationally, the percentage of unregistered children under the age of five has decreased from 12% (2014) to 8% (2018). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/02/2020
